'''Ticky tacky''' is generally the substance that little boxes on the hillside are made from.  These boxes have an uncanny tendency to look the same.  There have been reports of green ones, pink ones, blue ones and a yellow one.

Additionally, the people in the boxes tend to be made from the same substance as the boxes themselves, (that is, '''ticky tacky''').  It appears that there are doctors and lawyers and business executives, all of which are made out of '''ticky tacky''', and all of which look the same.  The children of these individuals often attend universities, where their component masses are broken down and reassembled out of '''ticky tacky'''.  After being broken down and reassembled, these children are all the same.

The American Heritage dictionary defines '''ticky tacky''' as "Shoddy material, as for the construction of standardized housing."  This definition is similar, but not identical to the true definition as stated above.  The American Heritage Dictionary is currently in the process of reviewing its defining practices and possibly updating the current definition of '''ticky tacky'''.